  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2023-01-23",
    "date": "2023-02-02T20:19:28Z",
    "text": "This bill prohibits the use of federal funds to allow an individual who is not a U.S. citizen to vote in any election in the District of Columbia (DC). Further, DC must certify that it does not allow noncitizens to vote in elections as a condition of receiving any federal funds.\n\nFederal law bars noncitizens from voting in federal elections; however, the DC Council passed a bill on October 18, 2022, that allows noncitizens who meet residency and other requirements to vote in local elections."
  },
